720
01:09:55,267 --> 01:09:58,699
Caspasian always said
you were a generous man.

721
01:09:59,666 --> 01:10:01,791
Well, Caspasian would know.

722
01:10:08,100 --> 01:10:11,930
You look like a tired old man
who's just come up out of the sea.

723
01:10:13,532 --> 01:10:15,657
Well, I've tried a little drowning.

724
01:10:16,599 --> 01:10:18,531
Let's try a little more.

725
01:10:19,300 --> 01:10:21,027
Come into my studio.

726
01:10:21,432 --> 01:10:24,523
I'll process your film
while you take a shower.

727
01:10:24,599 --> 01:10:28,396
We'll see which comes out of the bath
the more developed.

728
01:10:39,766 --> 01:10:41,959
When I first saw you, Stourley...

729
01:10:42,033 --> 01:10:44,897
at the Pantheon dinner
eight months ago...

730
01:10:45,000 --> 01:10:47,431
you reminded me of this painting.

731
01:10:47,499 --> 01:10:49,761
Andrea Doria.

732
01:10:50,267 --> 01:10:54,029
He had a belly,
and wasn't shy about showing it.

733
01:10:54,666 --> 01:10:56,859
He always fascinated me.

734
01:10:57,933 --> 01:11:02,298
And you, Stourley,
have proved to be just as fascinating.

735
01:11:04,466 --> 01:11:05,955
I can't paint.

736
01:11:06,599 --> 01:11:08,758
But I can take a photograph.

737
01:16:25,599 --> 01:16:26,724
Well.

738
01:16:35,166 --> 01:16:37,654
